┌──────────────────────── Screen Draw Loop ────────────────────────┐
│ 1) Draw HEADER once (3 lines, fixed positions)                   │
│ 2) Draw a rule line (the border)                                 │
│ 3) Draw BODY region (scrollable)                                 │
│ 4) On update:                                                    │
│    - Repaint HEADER only if its fields changed                   │
│    - Append OUTPUT to BODY with hard-wrapping at column 80       │
│    - Place PROMPT after the last wrapped line                    │
│    - Avoid full-screen clear; update only dirty regions          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


INPUT (any length) → split into tokens → wrap to 80 columns (visible width)
→ emit lines to BODY → write newline → place prompt at col 1 of next line








Daemon heartbeat → header status data

┌─────────────── Daemon (every ~10s) ───────────────┐
│  Ping Cloud  ──▶ cloud_status (OK/DEGRADED/OFF)   │
│  Ping AI     ──▶ ai_status (OK/DELAYED/OFF)       │
│  Check VPN   ──▶ vpn_status (ON/OFF)              │
│  (Optional)  ──▶ cpu_load, net_status             │
└───────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘
                │ publish (shared state / message bus)
                ▼
┌─────────────────────── CLI Renderer ────────────────────────────┐
│ Map statuses to colors (e.g., Checking=yellow, OK=white, OFF=grey) │
│ Update only header fields that changed (no full redraw)          │
│ Keep center zone for [STATE]; move last-cmd to line 3            │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘








